Bumi, Krakatau Steel, United Tractors: Indonesia Equity Preview

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-07-05T01:37:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-05/bumi-krakatau-steel-united-tractors-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies may
have unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  gained 0.7 percent to 3,953.52.  Coal producers: The price for thermal coal at the
Australian port of Newcastle, the benchmark for  Asia , climbed
0.7 percent to $120.40 a metric ton in the week ended July 1,
according to IHS McCloskey, a Petersfield, U.K.-based provider
of coal data. It was the second week of gains and the highest
price since the week ended May 6.  PT Bumi Resources (BUMI IJ), Asia’s biggest exporter of
thermal coal, declined 0.8 percent to 2,975 rupiah and PT Adaro
Energy (ADRO IJ),  Indonesia ’s second-largest coal producer, rose
1 percent to 2,525 rupiah.  PT Krakatau Steel (KRAS IJ): Indonesia’s biggest steel
producer will allocate $120 million to raise hot-strip mill
production to 3.5 million tons by 2014, from the current level
of 2.4 million tons, Investor Daily Indonesia reported, citing
President Director Fazwar Bujang. Krakatau Steel advanced 1
percent to 1,060 rupiah.  PT United Tractors (UNTR IJ): Indonesia’s largest heavy
equipment seller has raised its target for sales this year to
7,500 units from the previous 6,000 units,  Bisnis Indonesia 
reported, citing Corporate Secretary Sara Loebis. The company
sold 4,300 units of heavy equipment during the first half, the
report said. United Tractors rose 2 percent to 25,000 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at   dboey@bloomberg.net  